== Overview == The hills are bordered by the {{ill|Yamato River|ja|大和川|qq=draft|qq=draft}} to the north, the {{ill|Takadagawa River (Nara)|ja|高田川|qq=draft|qq=draft}} to the east, and the {{ill|Katsurage River|ja|葛下川|qq=draft|qq=draft}} to the west.<ref>{{Cite web|title=What is Umami Kyūryō?|url=https://kotobank.jp/word/%E9%A6%AC%E8%A6%8B%E4%B8%98%E9%99%B5-35130|website=Kotobank|accessdate=2021-02-07|language=ja|first=Britannica International Encyclopedia|last=Small Encyclopedia, Nipponica, World Encyclopedia}}</ref>
Within the hills are the {{ill|Umami Kofun Cluster|ja|馬見古墳群|1=Umami Kofun Cluster|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, including the nationally designated {{ill|Special Historic Site|ja|特別史跡|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|Suyama Kofun|ja|巣山古墳|1=Suyama Kofun|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. The area also hosts {{ill|Umami Kyūryō Park|ja|馬見丘陵公園|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. In recent years, residential developments such as {{ill|Nishi-Yamato New Town|ja|西大和ニュータウン|qq=draft|qq=draft}} have become prominent.
