'''Umami Kyūryō''' (馬見丘陵) is a hilly area composed of an alluvial terrace with an elevation of 70–80 meters, stretching north to south from [[:en:Kōryō, Nara|Kōryō, Nara]] to [[:en:Kawai, Nara|Kawai, Nara]] in the western part of the [[:en:Nara Basin|Nara Basin]], [[:en:Nara Prefecture|Nara Prefecture]], Japan.
== Overview == The hills are bordered by the [[:en:Yamato River|Yamato River]] to the north, the {{ill|Takadagawa River (Nara)|ja|高田川|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takadagawa River (Nara)|qq=}} to the east, and the {{ill|Katsurage River|ja|葛下川|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katsurage River|qq=}} to the west.<ref>{{Cite web|title=What is Umami Kyūryō?|url=https://kotobank.jp/word/%E9%A6%AC%E8%A6%8B%E4%B8%98%E9%99%B5-35130|website=Kotobank|accessdate=2021-02-07|language=ja|first=Britannica International Encyclopedia|last=Small Encyclopedia, Nipponica, World Encyclopedia}}</ref>
Within the hills are the {{ill|Umami Kofun Cluster|ja|馬見古墳群|1=Umami Kofun Cluster|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Umami Kofun Cluster|13=User:Immanuelle/Umami Kofun Cluster|qq=}}, including the nationally designated {{ill|Special Historic Site|ja|特別史跡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Special Historic Site|qq=}} [[:en:Suyama Kofun|Suyama Kofun]]. The area also hosts {{ill|Umami Kyūryō Park|ja|馬見丘陵公園|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Umami Kyūryō Park|qq=}}. In recent years, residential developments such as {{ill|Nishi-Yamato New Town|ja|西大和ニュータウン|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nishi-Yamato New Town|qq=}} have become prominent.
